<SCRIPT LANGUAGE="JavaScript" SRC="js/DataValidation.js"></SCRIPT><B CLASS="HeadlineText">Solstice Earring Quest</B><BR><BR><P><SPAN class=headers>EQHunter would like to give credit for this walkthrough to the folks at EQTraders and Xanthe Ravenwolf. For more tradeskill information, please visit them at <A href="http://www.eqtraders.com/"><FONT color=#0033ff>www.eqtraders.com</FONT></A>!</SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN class=headers>
<HR>
</SPAN><FONT size=2><FONT face=Garamond><SPAN class=headers>Xanthe`s Earring of Nature/PoTC Quest</SPAN> </FONT></FONT>
<P></P>
<P>
<P><FONT face=Garamond size=2>The original version of this quest, which relies very heavily on tradeskills, results in a copy of the druid spell (Protection of the Cabbage) and a no drop earring. The earring reward is: </FONT></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><A href="items/show_item.php?item=1111&amp;menustr="><STRONG><FONT color=#000000 face=Garamond size=2>Xanthe's Earring of N</FONT></STRONG></A><FONT size=2><FONT face=Garamond><STRONG>ature<BR></STRONG>LORE ITEM NO DROP <BR>Slot: EAR<BR>AC: 5<BR>STR: +8 &nbsp;&nbsp;STA: +8 &nbsp;&nbsp;WIS: +10 &nbsp;&nbsp;HP: +55 &nbsp;&nbsp;MANA: +55 &nbsp;&nbsp;<BR>SV FIRE: +7 &nbsp;&nbsp;SV COLD: +7 &nbsp;&nbsp;SV MAGIC: +7 &nbsp;&nbsp;<BR>Effect: Circle of combines (Must Equip. Casting Time:24.0)<BR>WT: 0.1 &nbsp;&nbsp;Size: TINY<BR>Class: DRU <BR>Race: ALL<BR></FONT></FONT></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><FONT face=Garamond size=2>If you have completed this quest and are not a druid, fear not! You can hand this earring back to Rebecca Cabbageleaf for: </FONT></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><A href="items/show_item.php?item=1770&amp;menustr="><FONT color=#000000 face=Garamond size=2><STRONG>Earring of the Solstice</STRONG></FONT></A><BR><FONT face=Garamond size=2>LORE ITEM NO DROP <BR>Slot: EAR<BR>AC: 5<BR>STA: +5 &nbsp;&nbsp;WIS: +8 &nbsp;&nbsp;INT: +8 &nbsp;&nbsp;HP: +55 &nbsp;&nbsp;MANA: +55 &nbsp;&nbsp;<BR>SV FIRE: +5 &nbsp;&nbsp;SV COLD: +5 &nbsp;&nbsp;SV MAGIC: +5 &nbsp;&nbsp;<BR>Recommended level of 51<BR>Effect: flowing thought I (worn)<BR>WT: 0.1 &nbsp;&nbsp;Size: TINY<BR>Class: ALL<BR>Race: ALL<BR></FONT></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><FONT size=2><FONT face=Garamond><I>(Yes, druids can do this quest twice, first trading in their Xanthe's Earring of Nature for the Earring of the Solstice, <B>then</B> completing the quest a second time for the Xanthe's Earring of Nature. Remember to trade the Xanthe's earring in before attempting the second quest combine, due to the lore flag)</I> </FONT></FONT></P>
<H3><FONT face=Garamond size=2>Some basic background:</FONT></H3>
<P><FONT face=Garamond size=2>On May 8, 2002, during the massive tradeskill patch, nine Liber Brassica Felix books were introduced throughout the lands, each written in a different language. They outlined various "gifts" from the three druid races, and gave hints as to the proper combination of them. The folks here at EQTC and the druids from the Druid's Grove did <I>much</I> pooling of knowledge to solve this <I>extremely</I> tradeskill-intensive quest. It was the first cross-server quest of it's kind, and once it was completed, the folks at VI stated that there would become an easier path to obtaining the spell. They also stated that the quest would stay in place for those who wished to strive and obtain the extra reward. (The first person to complete the quest it was the lovely Lady Xanthe Ravenwolf on Bertoxxulous, which explains the new name for the earring.) At that time, the reward was the spell, and a lovely little ALL/ALL no drop earring. </FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=Garamond size=2>On June 5, 2002 during another patch, the tenth Liber Brassica Felix book was found, and the old Earring of the Solstice magically changed into Xanthe's Earring of Nature in inventories throughout the lands. While greeted with some excitement, there was also much consternation by the non-druids in the community who suddenly found their all/all earring turn into something druid-only. Fortunately, VI took pity on all the frenzied tradeskillers who had spent the time and money to obtain the rather lovely earring, and announced partway through the day that Rebecca Cabbageleaf in Fungus Grove would be glad to accept trade-ins on earrings for something more suitable. (She could also be used to recharge earrings that were mistakenly out of charges, apparently by handing in the Xanthe's earring, then returning the Earring of the Solstice to her.) </FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=2><FONT face=Garamond><I><B>Please note that ALL of the "gifts" (and all the items that go into them) outlined in the links below are tradeable, so you can (and likely should) enlist the aid of grandmaster tradeskillers on your server for the items that are beyond your abilities.</B></I> </FONT></FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI><A href="page.asp?navid=131"><FONT color=#0033ff face=Garamond size=2>The Gifts of the Elves</FONT></A><FONT color=#0033ff face=Garamond size=2> </FONT>
<LI><A href="page.asp?navid=132"><FONT color=#0033ff face=Garamond size=2>The Gifts of Man</FONT></A><FONT color=#0033ff face=Garamond size=2> </FONT>
<LI><A href="page.asp?navid=133"><FONT color=#0033ff face=Garamond size=2>The Gifts of the Halflings</FONT></A><FONT color=#0033ff face=Garamond size=2> </FONT>
<LI><A href="page.asp?navid=134"><FONT color=#0033ff face=Garamond size=2>The Final Sacrifice</FONT></A><FONT color=#0033ff face=Garamond size=2> </FONT></LI></UL><BR><BR><BR clear=all>
